  "response": "The exact date of Jesus' birth is not recorded in the Bible, and there is no consensus among scholars regarding the specific year. However, most estimates place Jesus' birth between 6 and 4 BCE (Before Common Era). The traditional celebration of Jesus' birth is on **December 25**, which was officially established in the 4th century by the Christian church, though this date was likely chosen to coincide with existing pagan festivals like Saturnalia, rather than being based on historical evidence.\n\nThe year of Jesus' birth is often linked to the reign of Herod the Great, who died in 4 BCE. The Gospel of Matthew mentions that Herod was alive when Jesus was born, which suggests a birth date before 4 BCE. The exact day and month remain unknown.",
